</blockquote>

<p>An accelerometer <strong>is</strong> a sensor.</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>How can I use accelerometer to find displacement?</p>
</blockquote>

<p>By integrating twice, because acceleration is defined as the second derivative of position.</p>

<p>In a numerical calculation, in every step add the new value from the accelerometer to a sum (that's velocity) and add that sum to another sum, which will be the position. Also, the acceleration and velocity must both be multiplied by the change in time before summing.</p>

<pre><code>velocity += acceleration*dt
position += velocity*dt
</code></pre>
</p><br>
